                   <h1>Research Science Institute (Highschool)</h1>
                   
                        <p> 
                        From 2015-2022 I was the math faculty advisor for <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/highschool/rsi/index.html">RSI</a></b> with <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/~jerison/">David Jerison</a></b> and <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/directory/profile.html?pid=131">Tanya Khovanova</a></b>. We supervised eighty-three projects over the summers. You can find their final papers <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/highschool/rsi/past-projects.html">here</a></b>, some of which won various <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/highschool/rsi/index.html">awards</a></b> and scholarships.
                        
                                           <h1>Summer Program for Undergraduate Research</h1>
                   
                        <p> 
                        From 2015-2022 I was the math faculty advisor for <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/undergraduate/spur/index.html">SPUR and SPUR+</a></b> with <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/~jerison/">David Jerison</a></b>. We supervised over eighty-two projects over the summers and ran a <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/undergraduate/spur/lecture-series.html">lecture series</a></b> to expose students to mathematics research more broadly. You can find their final papers <b><a href="https://math.mit.edu/research/undergraduate/spur/past-projects.html">here</a></b>, some of which turned into published papers. 
                       


